verbs.description: outpick (third-person singular simple present outpicks, present participle outpicking, simple past and past participle outpicked)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To surpass in picking; to pick better or faster than.
examples: […]  the strongest people were not necessarily the fastest; men picked cotton, women picked cotton, children as young as ten picked cotton, and occasionally a woman came along who could outpick the men.
